    "created_at": "2017-02-23T12:01:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-02-23T12:01:36Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "On thinking about this a bit more, it's due to our use of win_unicode_console. We've effectively backported a change from Python 3.6. On 3.6 on Windows, [PYTHONIOENCODING](https://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#envvar-PYTHONIOENCODING) is ignored in a console unless `PYTHONLEGACYWINDOWSIOENCODING` is also set. Possibly we should add support for that environment variable to disable prompt_toolkit. I'll leave this issue open as a feature request for that, but mark it wishlist.\r\n\r\nOn Linux, setting PYTHONIOENCODING works as expected:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ PYTHONIOENCODING=ISO-8859-13 ipython -c \"import sys; print(sys.stdin.encoding)\"\r\nISO-8859-13\r\n$ PYTHONIOENCODING=ISO-8859-13 ipython -c \"import sys; print(sys.stdout.encoding)\"\r\nISO-8859-13\r\n```"
  }
